HEADWORD: Unbottomed
<hw>Un*bot"tomed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[1st
pref. <ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bottom</ets> + <ets>-ed</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Deprived of a bottom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not +
<ets>bottomed</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having no bottom; bottomless.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbound</ent>⟦br⟧
